Chevron Phillips to Shut Down Ethylene Unit at Port Arthur

-- B y   L e e l a   L a n d r e s s
-- 
2011-04-07T16:26:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/chevron-phillips-to-shut-down-ethylene-unit-at-port-arthur.html
Chevron Phillips Chemical Co. began
the planned shutdown of an ethylene unit at its chemical plant
in Port Arthur, Texas, according to a  filing  with state
regulators.  “Established procedures and practices will be followed to
safely shut down the process equipment,” The Woodlands, Texas-
based company said in the filing with the Texas Commission on
Environmental Quality.  Emissions associated with the shutdown began at 10:45 a.m.
local time and were expected to end on June 6 at the same time,
according to the filing.  Chevron Corp. (CVX)  and  ConocoPhillips (COP)  each own half of Chevron
Phillips Chemical Co. LLC, according to the company’s  website.   The Port Arthur plant is 93 miles (150 kilometers) east of
Houston.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leela Landress in Houston at 
 llandress@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
